Globe Exploration Drops Most in One Year on Ofek Drilling Delay

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-12-01T12:51:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/globe-exploration-drops-most-in-one-year-on-ofek-drilling-delay.html
Globe Exploration LP (GLEX)  declined the
most in more than a year after the oil and gas explorer said a
delay in a drilling test at the Ofek-1 well will cost an
estimated $2.4 million in damages.  The shares tumbled 20 percent, the biggest intraday decline
since September 2010, to 0.041 shekel at 2:44 p.m. in  Tel Aviv .  Globe reported a mechanical error at the Ofek-1 site,
according to a filing to the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
